MPC Settings:

--quality 7 (also known as Insane)

<-==============================->

About MPC:

MPC (aka Musepack) is far superior to MP3 in terms of quality and compression.

--quality 7 produces better audio quality than MP3s 
encoded with LAME with the -V 0 --vbr-new switch, 
while maintaining approximately the same filesize.

And many times, MPC audio at even lower settings 
than 7, or Insane, sounds better than MP3 would at 320-CBR. 

MPC is pure VBR and is designed to be as transparent as possible. 

<-=============================================================->

Winamp users:

Copy in_mpc.dll to the Winamp plugins folder, then restart Winamp.

Make sure you NEVER have the equalizer on when playing MPC!
It will mess up the sound, so make sure it is OFF!
